comments.body:
[~billie.rinaldi] thank you for the patch. This symmetric scenario will be a good one to open up for services. The patch looks good to me. +1 for it.

Just one comment on the error message -
{code}
  String ERROR_PLACEMENT_POLICY_TAG_INVALID = "Invalid target tag %s "
      + "specified in placement policy of component %s. Component %s must "
      + "also appear in placement policy of component %s with the same "
      + "constraint type.";
{code}
Since we are checking for scope in addition to constraint type, should we explicitly mention that in the error message too?
